        {
          "number": "4.13",
          "heading": "General savings provision",
          "body_text": "1.  The reenactment, revision, amendment, or repeal of a statute does not affect any of the following:\n  a.  The prior operation of the statute or any prior action taken under the statute.\n  b.  Any validation, cure, right, privilege, obligation, or liability previously acquired, accrued, accorded, or incurred under the statute.\n  c.  Any violation of the statute or penalty, forfeiture, or punishment incurred in respect to the statute, prior to the amendment or repeal.\n  d.  Any investigation, proceeding, or remedy in respect of any privilege, obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture, or punishment; and the investigation, proceeding, or remedy may be instituted, continued, or enforced, and the penalty, forfeiture, or punishment imposed, as if the statute had not been repealed or amended.\n  2.  If the penalty, forfeiture, or punishment for any offense is reduced by a reenactment, revision, or amendment of a statute, the penalty, forfeiture, or punishment if not already imposed shall be imposed according to the statute as amended.\n\neferred to in §124.201",
          "body_chars": 1070,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §4.13"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2008 Acts, ch 1031, §6\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "124.201"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/4.13.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/4.13.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/4.13.rtf"
        },
        {
          "number": "4.14",
          "heading": "General rules of construction for English language laws",
          "body_text": "It is presumed that English language requirements in the public sector are consistent with the laws of Iowa and any ambiguity in the English language text of the laws of Iowa shall be resolved, in accordance with the ninth and tenth amendments of the Constitution of the United States, not to deny or disparage rights retained by the people, and to reserve powers to the states or to the people.",
          "body_chars": 395,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2002 Acts, ch 1007, §2"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/4.14.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/4.14.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/4.14.rtf"
        }
      ],
      "url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/code/2026/4.rtf",
