          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.1.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.1.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.1.rtf"
        },
        {
          "number": "12C.2",
          "heading": "Approval — requirements",
          "body_text": "The approval of a financial institution as a depository of public funds for a public body shall be by written resolution or order that shall be entered of record in the minutes of the approving board, and that shall distinctly name each depository approved, and specify the maximum amount that may be kept on deposit in each depository.\n\n84 Acts, ch 1230, §6\nC93, §12C.2\neferred to in §12B.10",
          "body_chars": 392,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C24, 27, §139; C31, 35, §7420-d2; C39, §7420.02; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §453.2"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2002 Acts, ch 1096, §3, 17\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "12B.10"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.2.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.2.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.2.rtf"
        },
        {
          "number": "12C.3",
          "heading": "Reserved",
          "body_text": "",
          "body_chars": 0,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.3.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.3.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.3.rtf"
        },
        {
          "number": "12C.4",
          "heading": "Location of depositories",
          "body_text": "Deposits by the treasurer of state shall be in depositories located in this state; by a county officer or county public hospital officer or merged area hospital officer, in depositories located in the county or in an adjoining county within this state; by a memorial hospital treasurer, in a depository located within this state which shall be selected by the memorial hospital treasurer and approved by the memorial hospital commission; by a city treasurer or other city financial officer, in depositories located in the county in which the city is located or in an adjoining county, but if there is no depository in the county in which the city is located or in an adjoining county then in any other depository located in this state which shall be selected as a depository by the city council; by a school treasurer or by a school secretary in a depository within this state which shall be selected by the board of directors or the trustees of the school district; by a township clerk in a depository located within this state which shall be selected by the township clerk and approved by the trustees of the township. However, deposits may be made in depositories outside of Iowa for the purpose of paying principal and interest on bonded indebtedness of any municipality when the deposit is made not more than ten days before the date the principal or interest becomes due. Further, the treasurer of state may maintain an account or accounts outside the state of Iowa for the purpose of providing custodial services for the state and state retirement fund accounts. Deposits made for the purpose of completing an electronic financial transaction pursuant to section 8.89 or 331.427 may be made in any depository located in this state.\n\n84 Acts, ch 1230, §8; 86 Acts, ch 1243, §31\nC93, §12C.4\n; 2003 Acts, 1st Ex, ch 2, §35, 209\n; eferred to in §12B.10",
          "body_chars": 1855,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C24, 27, §139, 4319, 5548, 5651, 7404; C31, 35, §7420-d4; C39, §7420.04; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §453.4; 82 Acts, ch 1202, §2"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2003 Acts, ch 18, §2\n",
            "2013 Acts, ch 129, §27\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "12B.10"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.4.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.4.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.4.rtf"
        },
        {
          "number": "12C.5",
          "heading": "Refusal of deposits — procedure",
          "body_text": "If the approved depositories will not accept the deposits under the conditions prescribed or authorized in this chapter, the funds may be deposited, on the same or better terms as were offered to the depositories, in one or more approved depositories conveniently located within the state.\n\n84 Acts, ch 1230, §9\nC93, §12C.5\n;",
          "body_chars": 325,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C24, 27, §5653; C31, 35, §7420-d5; C39, §7420.05; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, 81, S81, §453.5; 81 Acts, ch 149, §1"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2001 Acts, ch 68, §3, 24",
            "2018 Acts, ch 1026, §7"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.5.pdf",
          "citation_html_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.5.html",
          "source_rtf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/12C.5.rtf"
        },
        {
          "number": "12C.6",
          "heading": "Interest rate — notice",
          "body_text": "1.  Public deposits shall be deposited with reasonable promptness in a depository legally designated as depository for the funds.\n  2.  a.  The treasurer of state, in consultation with subject matter experts as needed, shall establish a minimum rate to be earned on state funds placed in time deposits.\n  b.  State funds invested in depository time certificates of deposit shall draw interest at not less than the rate established, effective on the date of investment.\n  c.  An interest rate established by the treasurer of state under this section shall be in effect commencing on the eighth calendar day following the day the rate is established and until a different rate is established and takes effect.\n  d.  The treasurer of state shall give advisory notice of an interest rate established under this section. This notice may be given by publication in one or more newspapers, by publication in the Iowa administrative bulletin, by ordinary mail to persons directly affected, by any other method determined by the treasurer of state, or by a combination of these. In all cases, the notice shall be published in the Iowa administrative bulletin.\n  e.  The notice shall contain the following words:\nThe rate of interest has been determined by the treasurer of state of the state of Iowa to be the minimum interest rate that shall be paid on public funds deposited in approved financial institutions. To be eligible to accept deposits of public funds of the state of Iowa, a financial institution shall demonstrate a commitment to serve the needs of the local community in which it is chartered to do business. These needs include credit services as well as deposit services. All such financial institutions are required to provide the treasurer of state with a written description of their commitment to provide credit services in the community. This statement is available for examination by citizens.\n  f.  The notice shall also provide the name and address of a state official to whom inquiries can be sent. Actions of the treasurer of state under this section are exempt from chapter 17A.\n  3.  Public funds invested in depositories’ time certificates of deposit by a public body or officer other than the treasurer of state shall draw interest at rates to be determined by the public body or officer and the depository, which rates shall not be less than the minimum rate set under this section for state funds.\n\n84 Acts, ch 1230, §10\nC93, §12C.6\n96 Acts, ch 1021, §1; ; ; eferred to in §12B.10, 12C.7, 384.58, 573.12, 573.14, 602.8109\nFor interest rates on public obligations and special assessments, see §74A.6\nSubsection 2, paragraph f amended",
          "body_chars": 2655,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C24, 27, §140, 4319, 5548, 5651, 7404; C31, 35, §7420-d6; C39, §7420.06; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, 81, S81, §453.6; 81 Acts, ch 39, §2, ch 149, §2"
