          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/232.160.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "232.161",
          "heading": "Department as authority in receiving state",
          "body_text": "As used in paragraph “a” of article V of the interstate compact on the placement of children under section 232.158, the phrase “appropriate authority in the receiving state” with reference to this state means the state department of health and human services.\n\n83 Acts, ch 96, §157, 159\n85 Acts, ch 173, §30\nCS85, §232.161\n; eferred to in §232.166, 232.167",
          "body_chars": 356,
