          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/232.164.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "232.165",
          "heading": "Executive head",
          "body_text": "As used in article VII of the interstate compact on the placement of children, section 232.158, the term “executive head” means the governor. The governor is hereby authorized to appoint a compact administrator in accordance with the terms of article VII of that interstate compact.\n\n85 Acts, ch 173, §30\nCS85, §232.165\neferred to in §232.166, 232.167",
          "body_chars": 351,
          "history_brackets": [
