            "2008 Acts, ch 1032, §201",
            "2023 Acts, ch 19, §639 "
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "232.172"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/232.171.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "232.172",
          "heading": "Confinement of delinquent juvenile",
          "body_text": "1.  For a juvenile under the jurisdiction of this state who is subject to the interstate compact for juveniles under section 232.173, the confinement of the juvenile in an institution located within another compacting state shall be as provided under the compact.\n  2.  This subsection applies to the confinement of a delinquent juvenile under the jurisdiction of this state in an institution located within a noncompacting state, as defined in section 232.173, that entered into the interstate compact on juveniles under section 232.171. In addition to any institution in which the authorities of this state may otherwise confine or order the confinement of the delinquent juvenile, such authorities may, pursuant to the out-of-state confinement amendment to the interstate compact on juveniles in section 232.171, confine or order the confinement of the delinquent juvenile in a compact institution within another party state.\n\nCS85, §232.172\n;",
          "body_chars": 946,
