        {
          "number": "455B.211",
          "heading": "Definitions",
          "body_text": "When used in this part 2 of subchapter III, unless the context otherwise requires:\n  1.  “Certificate” means the certificate of competence issued by the director stating that the operator has met the requirements for the specified operator classification of the certification program.\n  2.  “Operator” means a person who has direct responsibility for the operation of a water treatment plant, water distribution system, or waste water treatment plant.\n  3.  “Waste water treatment plant” means the facility or group of units used for the treatment of waste water from public sewer systems and for the reduction and handling of solids removed from such wastes.\n  4.  “Water distribution system” means that portion of the water supply system in which water is conveyed from the water treatment plant or other supply point to the premises of the consumer.\n  5.  “Water supply system” means the system of pipes, structures, and facilities through which a public water supply is obtained, treated and sold or distributed for human consumption or household use.\n  6.  “Water treatment plant” means that portion of the water supply system which in some way alters the physical, chemical, or bacteriological quality of the water.\n\nC83, §455B.211\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1890; eferred to in §272C.1",
          "body_chars": 1284,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.1; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.50"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2021 Acts, ch 76, §150\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.211.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.212",
          "heading": "Director’s duties",
          "body_text": "The director shall classify all water treatment plants, water distribution systems, and waste water treatment plants affecting the public welfare with regard to the size, type, character of water and waste water to be treated and other physical conditions affecting such treatment plants and distribution systems, and according to the skill, knowledge, and experience that an operator must have to supervise the operation of the facilities to protect the public health and prevent pollution. The director may appoint advisory committees to advise the department in carrying out the requirements of this part.\n\nC83, §455B.212\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1891, 1899",
          "body_chars": 654,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.2; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.51"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.212.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.213",
          "heading": "Certification of operators",
          "body_text": "1.  By director.  The director shall certify persons as to their qualifications to supervise the operation of treatment plants and water distribution systems after considering the recommendations of the commission.\n  2.  Applications.  Applications for certification shall be on forms prescribed and furnished by the department and shall not contain a recent photograph of the applicant. An applicant is not ineligible for certification because of age, citizenship, sex, race, religion, marital status, or national origin although the application may require citizenship information. The director may consider the past felony record of an applicant only if the felony conviction relates directly to the practice of operation of waterworks or wastewater works. Character references may be required, but shall not be obtained from certificate holders.\n  3.  Disclosure of confidential information.  An employee of the department shall not disclose information relating to the following:\n  a.  Criminal history or prior misconduct of the applicant.\n  b.  Information relating to the contents of the examination to persons other than members of a board of certification of another state or their employees or an employee of the department.\n  c.  Information relating to the examination results other than final scores except for information about the results of an examination which is given to the person who took the examination.\n  4.  Violation.\n  a.  An employee of the department who willfully communicates or seeks to communicate such information, and a person who willfully requests, obtains, or seeks to obtain such information, is guilty of a simple misdemeanor.\n  b.  A member of the commission who willfully communicates or seeks to communicate such information, and any person who willfully requests, obtains, or seeks to obtain such information, is guilty of a public offense which is punishable by a fine not exceeding one hundred dollars or by imprisonment in the county jail for not more than thirty days.\n\nC83, §455B.213\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1892, 1899; 88 Acts, ch 1134, §85; eferred to in §272C.1",
          "body_chars": 2109,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.3; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.52"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2011 Acts, ch 25, §103\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.213.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.214",
          "heading": "and 455B.215Reserved",
          "body_text": "",
          "body_chars": 0,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.214.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.216",
          "heading": "Examinations",
          "body_text": "The director shall hold at least one examination each year for the purpose of examining candidates for certification at a time and place designated by the director. Any written examination may be given by the department. All examinations in theory shall be in writing and the identity of the person taking the examination shall be concealed until after the examination papers have been graded. For examinations in practice, the identity of the person taking the examination shall also be concealed as far as possible. Those applicants whose competency is acceptable shall be recommended for certification. Applicants who fail the examination shall be allowed to take the examination at the next scheduled time. Thereafter, the applicant shall be allowed to take the examination at the discretion of the director. An applicant who has failed the examination may request in writing information from the department concerning the applicant’s examination grade and subject areas or questions which the applicant failed to answer correctly, except that if the director administers a uniform, standardized examination, the director is only required to provide the examination grade and the other information concerning the applicant’s examination results which is available to the department.\n\nC83, §455B.216\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1893; eferred to in §272C.1",
          "body_chars": 1349,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.7; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.56"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2016 Acts, ch 1073, §124\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.216.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.217",
          "heading": "Operator’s certificate",
          "body_text": "When the director is satisfied that an applicant is qualified by examination or otherwise, the director shall issue a certificate attesting to the competency of the applicant as an operator. The certificate shall indicate the classification of works which the operator is qualified to supervise.\n\nC83, §455B.217\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1894",
          "body_chars": 335,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.9; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.57"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.217.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.218",
          "heading": "Duration of certificates — fee — renewal",
          "body_text": "Certificates shall be for the multiyear period determined by the director unless sooner revoked by the director, but the certificates remain the property of the department and the certificate shall so state. The fee for issuance of certificates as determined under section 455B.221 shall be prorated on a quarterly basis for any original certificate issued for a period of less than twelve months. A person who fails to renew a certificate prior to its expiration shall be allowed to renew it within thirty days following its expiration, but the director may assess a reasonable penalty as established by rule.\n\nC83, §455B.218\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1895",
          "body_chars": 650,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.10; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.58"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.218.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.219",
          "heading": "Revocation or suspension",
          "body_text": "The director may suspend or revoke the certificate of an operator, following a hearing before the director, when the operator is guilty of the following acts or offenses:\n  1.  Fraud in procuring a license.\n  2.  Professional incompetency.\n  3.  Knowingly making misleading, deceptive, untrue or fraudulent representations in the practice of the operator’s profession or engaging in unethical conduct or practice harmful or detrimental to the public. Proof of actual injury need not be established.\n  4.  Habitual intoxication or addiction to the use of drugs.\n  5.  Conviction of a felony related to the profession or occupation of the licensee, or the conviction of any felony that would affect the licensee’s ability to operate a water treatment or wastewater treatment plant. A copy of the record of conviction or plea of guilty shall be conclusive evidence.\n  6.  Fraud in representation as to skill or ability.\n  7.  Use of untruthful or improbable statements in advertisements.\n  8.  Willful or repeated violations of this subchapter III.\n\nC83, §455B.219\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1896; eferred to in §272C.1, 272C.3, 272C.4\n\n455B.220  Certificate without examination.  Repealed by \n.",
          "body_chars": 1184,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.11; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.59"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2021 Acts, ch 76, §99\nR",
            "2006 Acts, ch 1014, §10\n"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1",
            "272C.3",
            "272C.4"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.219.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.221",
          "heading": "Certification and examination fees",
          "body_text": "The director may charge a fee for certificates issued under this part. The fee for the certificates and for renewal shall be based on the costs of administering and enforcing this part and paying the expenses of the department relating to certification. The department shall be reimbursed for all costs incurred. The director shall set a fee for the examination which shall be based upon the annual cost of administering the examinations. All fees collected shall be retained by the department for administration of the certification program.\n\nC83, §455B.221\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1897; 94 Acts, ch 1059, §1",
          "body_chars": 604,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.14; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.61"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1",
            "455B.218"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.221.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.222",
          "heading": "Rules",
          "body_text": "The commission may adopt rules as are necessary to carry out this part.\n\nC83, §455B.222\n86 Acts, ch 1245, §1898",
          "body_chars": 111,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.15; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.62"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.222.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.223",
          "heading": "Competent operator required",
          "body_text": "It shall be unlawful for any person, firm, corporation, municipal corporation, or other governmental subdivision or agency, operating a water treatment plant, water distribution system, or wastewater treatment plant to operate same unless the competency of the operator to operate such plant or system is duly certified to by the director under the provisions of this part 2 of subchapter III. It shall also be unlawful for any person to perform the duties of an operator, as defined in this part, without being duly certified under the provisions of  this part.\n\nC83, §455B.223\n; eferred to in §272C.1, 455B.199D",
          "body_chars": 613,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.16; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.63"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2021 Acts, ch 76, §150",
            "2021 Acts, ch 80, §283\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.1",
            "455B.199D"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.223.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "455B.224",
          "heading": "Simple misdemeanor",
          "body_text": "Any person, including any firm, corporation, municipal corporation, or other governmental subdivision or agency, violating any provisions of this part 2 of subchapter III or the rules adopted under this part after written notice of the violation by the director is guilty of a simple misdemeanor. Each day of operation in such violation of  this part or any rules adopted under this part shall constitute a separate offense. It shall be the duty of the appropriate county attorney to secure injunctions of continuing violations of any provisions of  this part or the rules adopted under this part.\n\nC83, §455B.224\n; ; eferred to in §272C.1, 331.756(58)",
          "body_chars": 652,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C66, 71, §136A.17; C73, 75, 77, 79, 81, §455B.64"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2021 Acts, ch 76, §100",
            "2021 Acts, ch 80, §284",
            "2023 Acts, ch 64, §69\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/455B.224.pdf"
        },
        {
