        {
          "number": "600.6",
          "heading": "Attachments to an adoption petition",
          "body_text": "An adoption petition shall have attached to it the following:\n  1.  A certified copy of the birth certificate showing parentage of the person to be adopted or, if such certificate is not available, a verified birth record. The department shall provide a certified copy of a birth certificate or a verified birth record, as applicable, to the person adopting a child when the department is the guardian of the child.\n  2.  A copy of any order terminating parental rights with respect to the person to be adopted.\n  3.  If parental rights were terminated pursuant to chapter 232, a copy of any court orders concerning whether ongoing contact between siblings not placed with the person to be adopted is in the best interest of each sibling.\n  4.  Any written consent and verified statement required under section 600.7, except the consent required under subsection 1, paragraph “d”, of that section.\n  5.  Any preplacement investigation report that has been prepared at the time of filing pursuant to section 600.8.\n  6.  In the case of a standby adoption as defined in section 600.14A, a form completed by the terminally ill parent consenting to termination of parental rights and adoption of the child by a person or persons specified in the consent form, effective at a future date when the terminally ill parent of the child has died or requests that a final adoption decree be issued.\n\n89 Acts, ch 140, §1; 99 Acts, ch 43, §1; ; ; ; eferred to in §600.14A",
          "body_chars": 1458,
          "history_brackets": [
            "R60, §2601; C73, §2308; C97, §3251; C24, §10497; C27, 31, 35, §10501-b3; C39, §10501.3; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, §600.3; C77, 79, 81, §600.6"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2001 Acts, ch 57, §3",
            "2022 Acts, ch 1096, §7",
            "2023 Acts, ch 134, §2",
            "2024 Acts, ch 1043, §102\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "600.14A"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/600.6.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "600.6A",
          "heading": "Court determination regarding appointment of guardian ad litem",
          "body_text": "Prior to ordering a hearing on the adoption petition, the court shall make a determination of the need for a guardian ad litem for a minor child to be adopted and shall, in writing, either appoint or waive the appointment of a guardian ad litem for purposes of the adoption proceeding in the order setting the adoption hearing.",
          "body_chars": 327,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2016 Acts, ch 1069, §2"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/600.6A.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "600.7",
          "heading": "Consents to the adoption",
          "body_text": "1.  An adoption petition shall not be granted unless the following persons consent to the adoption or unless the juvenile court or court makes a determination under subsection 4:\n  a.  Any guardian of the person to be adopted.\n  b.  The spouse of a petitioner who is a stepparent.\n  c.  The spouse of a petitioner who is separately petitioning to adopt an adult person.\n  d.  The person to be adopted if that person is fourteen years of age or older.\n  2.  A consent to the adoption shall be in writing, shall name the person to be adopted and the petitioner, shall be signed by the person consenting, and shall be made in the following manner:\n  a.  If by any minor person to be adopted who is fourteen years of age or older, in the presence of the juvenile court or court in which the adoption petition is filed.\n  b.  If by any other person, either in the presence of the juvenile court or court in which the adoption petition is filed or before a notary public as provided in chapter 9B.\n  3.  A consent to the adoption may be withdrawn prior to the issuance of an adoption decree under section 600.13 by the filing of an affidavit of consent withdrawal with the juvenile court or court. Such affidavit shall be treated in the same manner as an attached verified statement is treated under subsection 4.\n  4.  If any person required to consent under this section refuses to or cannot be located to give consent, the petitioner may attach to the petition a verified statement of such refusal or lack of location. The juvenile court or court shall then determine, at the adoption hearing prescribed in section 600.12, whether, in the best interests of the person to be adopted and the petitioner, any particular consent shall be unnecessary to the granting of an adoption petition.\n\n– 9; eferred to in §600.6, 600.11, 600.14A",
          "body_chars": 1827,
          "history_brackets": [
            "R60, §2600, 2601; C73, §2307, 2308; C97, §3250, 3251; C24, §10496, 10497; C27, 31, 35, §10501-b1, 10501-b3; C39, §10501.1, 10501.3; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, §600.1, 600.3; C77, 79, 81, §600.7"
          ],
