    {
      "chapter": "709",
      "chapter_title": "SEXUAL ABUSE",
      "rtf_bytes": 140551,
      "text_chars": 45054,
      "section_count": 24,
      "sections": [
        {
          "number": "709.1",
          "heading": "Sexual abuse defined",
          "body_text": "Any sex act between persons is sexual abuse by either of the persons when the act is performed with the other person in any of the following circumstances:\n  1.  The act is done by force or against the will of the other. If the consent or acquiescence of the other is procured by threats of violence toward any person or if the act is done while the other is under the influence of a drug inducing sleep or is otherwise in a state of unconsciousness, the act is done against the will of the other.\n  2.  Such other person is suffering from a mental defect or incapacity which precludes giving consent, or lacks the mental capacity to know the right and wrong of conduct in sexual matters.\n  3.  Such other person is a child.\n\n84 Acts, ch 1188, §1; 99 Acts, ch 159, §1\n\nDefinition of sex act, §702.17",
          "body_chars": 799,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C51, §2581, 2583; R60, §4204, 4206; C73, §3861, 3863; C97, §4756, 4758; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, §12966, 12967; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, §698.1, 698.3; C79, 81, §709.1"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "232.116",
            "600A.8",
            "611.23",
            "614.1",
            "668.15",
            "692A.101",
            "692A.102",
            "713.3",
            "915.40"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.1.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.1A",
          "heading": "Incapacitation",
          "body_text": "As used in this chapter, “incapacitated” means a person is disabled or deprived of ability, as follows:\n  1.  “Mentally incapacitated” means that a person is temporarily incapable of apprising or controlling the person’s own conduct due to the influence of a narcotic, anesthetic, or intoxicating substance.\n  2.  “Physically helpless” means that a person is unable to communicate an unwillingness to act because the person is unconscious, asleep, or is otherwise physically limited.\n  3.  “Physically incapacitated” means that a person has a bodily impairment or handicap that substantially limits the person’s ability to resist or flee.\n99 Acts, ch 159, §2",
          "body_chars": 658,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.1A.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.2",
          "heading": "Sexual abuse in the first degree",
          "body_text": "1.  A person commits sexual abuse in the first degree when in the course of committing sexual abuse the person causes another serious injury.\n  2.  Sexual abuse in the first degree is a class “A” felony.\n\neferred to in §321.375, 622.31B, 664A.2, 664A.3, 692A.101, 692A.102, 709.19, 903B.10\nDefinition of forcible felony, §702.11",
          "body_chars": 328,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C51, §2581; R60, §4204; C73, §3861; C97, §4756; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, §12966; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, §698.1; C79, 81, §709.2"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2018 Acts, ch 1041, §127\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "321.375",
            "622.31B",
            "664A.2",
            "664A.3",
            "692A.101",
            "692A.102",
            "709.19",
            "903B.10"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.2.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.3",
          "heading": "Sexual abuse in the second degree",
          "body_text": "1.  A person commits sexual abuse in the second degree when the person commits sexual abuse under any of the following circumstances:\n  a.  During the commission of sexual abuse the person displays in a threatening manner a dangerous weapon, or uses or threatens to use force creating a substantial risk of death or serious injury to any person.\n  b.  The other person is a child.\n  c.  The person is aided or abetted by one or more persons and the sex act is committed by force or against the will of the other person against whom the sex act is committed.\n  2.  Sexual abuse in the second degree is a class “B” felony.\n\n84 Acts, ch 1188, §2; 99 Acts, ch 159, §3; ; eferred to in §321.375, 622.31B, 664A.2, 664A.3, 692A.101, 692A.102, 709.19, 709.23, 901A.2, 902.12, 902.14, 903B.10, 906.15\nDefinition of child, §702.5\nDefinition of forcible felony, §702.11\nDefinition of sex act, §702.17",
          "body_chars": 889,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C51, §2581; R60, §4204; C73, §3861; C97, §4756; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, §12966; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, §698.1; C79, 81, §709.3"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2013 Acts, ch 90, §228",
            "2021 Acts, ch 37, §3\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "321.375",
            "622.31B",
            "664A.2",
            "664A.3",
            "692A.101",
            "692A.102",
            "709.19",
            "709.23",
            "901A.2",
            "902.12",
            "902.14",
            "903B.10",
            "906.15"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.3.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.4",
          "heading": "Sexual abuse in the third degree",
          "body_text": "1.  A person commits sexual abuse in the third degree when the person performs a sex act under any of the following circumstances:\n  a.  The act is done by force or against the will of the other person, whether or not the other person is the person’s spouse or is cohabiting with the person.\n  b.  The act is between persons who are not at the time cohabiting as husband and wife and if any of the following are true:\n  (1)  The other person is suffering from a mental defect or incapacity which precludes giving consent.\n  (2)  The other person is fourteen or fifteen years of age and any of the following are true:\n  (a)  The person is a member of the same household as the other person.\n  (b)  The person is related to the other person by blood or affinity to the fourth degree.\n  (c)  The person is in a position of authority over the other person and uses that authority to coerce the other person to submit.\n  (d)  The person is four or more years older than the other person.\n  c.  The act is performed while the other person is under the influence of a controlled substance, which may include but is not limited to flunitrazepam, and all of the following are true:\n  (1)  The controlled substance, which may include but is not limited to flunitrazepam, prevents the other person from consenting to the act.\n  (2)  The person performing the act knows or reasonably should have known that the other person was under the influence of the controlled substance, which may include but is not limited to flunitrazepam.\n  d.  The act is performed while the other person is mentally incapacitated, physically incapacitated, or physically helpless.\n  2.  Sexual abuse in the third degree is a class “C” felony.\n\n89 Acts, ch 138, §3; 94 Acts, ch 1128, §1; 97 Acts, ch 78, §1; 99 Acts, ch 159, §4; ; eferred to in §272C.15, 321.375, 622.31B, 664A.2, 664A.3, 692A.101, 692A.102, 692A.121, 692A.128, 702.11, 709.19, 902.14, 903B.10, 906.15\nDefinition of forcible felony, see §702.11 \nDefinition of sex act, see §702.17",
          "body_chars": 2012,
          "history_brackets": [
            "C51, §2581, 2583; R60, §4204, 4206; C73, §3861, 3863; C97, §4756, 4758; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, §12966, 12967; C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, 66, 71, 73, 75, 77, §698.1, 698.3; C79, 81, §709.4"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2013 Acts, ch 30, §201",
            "2021 Acts, ch 37, §4\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "272C.15",
            "321.375",
            "622.31B",
