            "692A.101",
            "692A.102",
            "709.19",
            "802.2B",
            "903B.10"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.11.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.12",
          "heading": "Indecent contact with a child",
          "body_text": "1.  A person eighteen years of age or older is upon conviction guilty of an aggravated misdemeanor if the person commits any of the following acts with a child, not the person’s spouse, with or without the child’s consent, for the purpose of arousing or satisfying the sexual desires of either of them:\n  a.  Fondle or touch the inner thigh, groin, buttock, anus, or breast of the child.\n  b.  Touch the clothing covering the immediate area of the inner thigh, groin, buttock, anus, or breast of the child.\n  c.  Solicit or permit a child to fondle or touch the inner thigh, groin, buttock, anus, or breast of the person.\n  d.  Solicit a child to engage in any act prohibited under section 709.8, subsection 1, paragraph “a”, “b”, or “e”.\n  2.  The provisions of this section shall also apply to a person sixteen or seventeen years of age who commits any of the enumerated acts with a child who is at least five years the person’s junior, in which case the juvenile court shall have jurisdiction under chapter 232.\n\n85 Acts, ch 181, §2; 88 Acts, ch 1252, §4; eferred to in §622.31B, 692A.102, 709.19, 802.2B, 903B.10",
          "body_chars": 1116,
          "history_brackets": [
            "81 Acts, ch 204, §7"
          ],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2013 Acts, ch 30, §203\nR"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [
            "622.31B",
            "692A.102",
            "709.19",
            "802.2B",
            "903B.10"
          ],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.12.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.13",
          "heading": "Child in need of assistance complaints",
          "body_text": "During or following an investigation into allegations of violations of this chapter or of chapter 726 or 728 involving an alleged victim under the age of eighteen and an alleged offender who is not a person responsible for the care of the alleged victim, anyone with knowledge of the alleged offense may file a complaint pursuant to section 232.83 alleging the alleged victim to be a child in need of assistance as defined under section 232.2. In all cases, the complaint shall be filed by any peace officer with knowledge of the investigation when the peace officer has reason to believe that the alleged victim may require treatment as a result of the alleged offense and that the alleged victim’s parent, guardian, or custodian will be unwilling or unable to provide the treatment.\n88 Acts, ch 1252, §5;",
          "body_chars": 806,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2021 Acts, ch 80, §374"
          ],
          "referred_to_in": [],
          "citation_pdf_url": "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/ico/section/2026/709.13.pdf"
        },
        {
          "number": "709.14",
          "heading": "Lascivious conduct with a minor",
          "body_text": "1.  a.  It is unlawful for a person eighteen years of age or older who is in a position of authority over a minor to force, persuade, or coerce that minor, with or without consent, to disrobe or partially disrobe for the purpose of arousing or satisfying the sexual desires of either of them.\n  b.  A violation of this subsection is a serious misdemeanor.\n  2.  For purposes of subsections 3 and 4, “minor” means a person fourteen or fifteen years of age.\n  3.  a.  It is unlawful for a person eighteen years of age or older who is in a position of authority over a minor to perform any of the following acts with that minor, with or without consent, for the purpose of arousing or satisfying the sexual desires of either of them:\n  (1)  Fondle or touch the inner thigh, groin, buttock, anus, or breast of the minor.\n  (2)  Touch the clothing covering the immediate area of the inner thigh, groin, buttock, anus, or breast of the minor.\n  (3)  Solicit or permit the minor to fondle or touch the inner thigh, groin, buttock, anus, or breast of the person.\n  (4)  Solicit the minor to engage in any act prohibited under subsection 4, paragraph “a”, subparagraph (1), (2), or (3).\n  b.  A violation of this subsection is a serious misdemeanor. \n  4.  a.  It is unlawful for a person eighteen years of age or older who is in a position of authority over a minor to perform any of the following acts with that minor, with or without consent, for the purpose of arousing or satisfying the sexual desires of either of them:\n  (1)  Fondle or touch the pubes or genitals of the minor. \n  (2)  Permit or cause the minor to fondle or touch the person’s genitals or pubes.\n  (3)  Cause the touching of the person’s genitals to any part of the body of the minor.\n  (4)  Solicit the minor to engage in a sex act or solicit a person to arrange a sex act with the minor. \n  (5)  Inflict pain or discomfort upon the minor or permit the minor to inflict pain or discomfort on the person. \n  b.  A violation of this subsection is an aggravated misdemeanor. \n89 Acts, ch 105, §2; ; eferred to in §622.31B, 692A.102, 709.19, 802.2B, 903B.10",
          "body_chars": 2119,
          "history_brackets": [],
          "acts_citations": [
            "2018 Acts, ch 1041, §127",
            "2019 Acts, ch 114, §1\nR"
          ],
